classes.name: NSXConnectionManager
classes.description: Exposes operations that can be performed on NSX Connections

methods.name: syncNsxConnection
methods.parameters: connection: NSXConnection
methods.description: Synchronises the NSX Endpoint properties. After an endpoint is created, certain properties of NSX may change. E.g. version, role etc. This method refreshes these properties by querying NSX and updating the properties. The properties that are synced are version, role and related endpoints.

methods.description: Deletes all endpoints

methods.parameters: name: string, username: string, password: string, url: string, retryCount: number, connTimeout: number
methods.description: Creates a new NSX Endpoint

methods.description: Finds a connection from the Connection Repository, given its id

methods.name: findConnectionByName
methods.parameters: name: string
methods.description: Finds a connection from the Connection Repository, given its name

methods.name: serialize
methods.parameters: obj: any, format: string

classes.name: NSXNatManager
classes.description: Exposes scriptable APIs for configuring NAT service on an NSX edge

methods.name: applyNatConfiguration
methods.parameters: connection: NSXConnection, edge: NSXEdge, natRules: NSXNatRule[]
methods.description: This method configures NAT service on an NSX edge. It can be used to add new NAT rules to existing NAT configuration or to modify or delete existing NAT rules from the configuration. For new rules, ruleId field is not specified. For rules to be deleted, set value of action field to 'delete'.

methods.name: getNatRules
methods.parameters: connection: NSXConnection, edge: NSXEdge
methods.description: This method retrieves the NAT rules configured on the NSX edge.

methods.name: deleteNatRules
methods.parameters: connection: NSXConnection, edgeId: string, ruleIds: number[]
methods.description: This method deletes specified NAT rules from the NSX edge. Rule ids of the NAT rules to be deleted are provided as input parameters.

methods.name: addNatRules
methods.parameters: connection: NSXConnection, edgeId: string, natRules: NSXNatRule[]
methods.description: This method adds NAT rules to a given NSX edge.
